amwork is critical.\n**Remaining uncertainty:** How severe C\u2019s egocentric behavior is in day\u2011to\u2011day crew dynamics; whether his reluctance to pursue further education will limit adaptability to evolving long\u2011haul operations; and whether B\u2019s interpersonal issues (pretentiousness, nasty remarks, weak numeric memory) materially impair safety or crew morale.\n**What would change my vote:** Concrete evidence that A or D consistently demonstrate strong teamwork/communication; or evidence that B\u2019s interpersonal flaws are minor and his technical reliability outweighs the lack of teamwork data; or evidence that C\u2019s egocentric traits lead to significant crew conflict or that his lack of further education hampers long\u2011term performance.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce final answer as per instructions. We are agent_3. We must give PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with our vote. We need to consider the discussion so far. Agent_3 previously gave provisional preference Candidate B. Now after seeing others' votes (C from agents 1 and 2) and new info (C has positive crew atmosphere), we may reconsider. We must follow grounding rule: only use explicit attributes. We have candidate attributes list and revealed facts. We have also other agents' statements. We can incorporate that.\n\nWe need to decide current preferred candidate. We can either stick with B or switch to C. Let's weigh.\n\nCandidate B strengths: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather, excellent computer skills. Weaknesses: pretentious, wrong tone, weak numeric memory, nasty remarks. No explicit teamwork strength.\n\nCandidate C strengths: quick correct decisions, puts concern for others above everything, excellent attention skills, creates positive atmosphere with crew (teamwork), 100% reliable. Weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education.\n\nLong-distance pilot requires teamwork/communication heavily. C has explicit positive crew atmosphere, which is a strong indicator. B lacks any positive teamwork evidence and has negative interpersonal behavior. C's communication difficulty is a weakness but he still creates positive atmosphere, indicating perhaps effective communication in practice. Egocentric and lack of further education are concerns for long-term development but may be less safety-critical than B's nasty remarks and weak numeric memory.\n\nThus I think C is now the best candidate. So we should update vote to Candidate C.\n\nWe need to produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing key evidence, evidence from others, major alternatives, main tradeoff, remaining uncertainty, what would change vote. Also include confidence.\n\nWe must reference that other agents (1 and 2) favor C, and agent 3 previously favored B. Provide reasoning.\n\nNow produce final output."}
